## Consequences

### Positive

- Clear, opinionated stack reduces decision fatigue for all contributors
- Type safety catches errors before runtime
- Documented conventions enable AI-assisted development
- Performance-first defaults (Server Components, `next/image`, `next/font`)

### Negative

- Opinionated choices mean friction if a team member prefers a different tool
- App Router has a steeper learning curve than the Pages Router
- {{ state_management }} and {{ api_client }} are separate concerns - the team must understand when to use each

### Risks

- Next.js App Router caching behaviour changed significantly in Next.js 15 - review the [Next.js 15 upgrade guide](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/upgrading/version-15) if upgrading
- New contributors should read `docs/architecture.md` before writing any code

